        <num>CC 622</num>
        <heading>622.  Confusion of usufruct and naked ownership</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 622.  Confusion of usufruct and naked ownership.
A usufruct terminates by confusion when the usufruct and the naked ownership are united in the same person.
The usufruct does not terminate if the title by which the usufruct and the naked ownership were united is annulled for some previously existing defect or some vice inherent in the act.</p>
        </content>
